# Notification Parsing Patterns

## Parser Architecture

Each financial app has a dedicated parser module following this contract:

```ts
type ParsedTransaction = {
  amount: number;
  currency: string;
  merchant: string;
  type: 'income' | 'expense';
  sourceApp: string;
  rawNotification: string;
  confidence: number;
};

type NotificationParser = {
  appPackage: string;
  parse: (title: string, body: string) => ParsedTransaction | null;
};
```

## Parser Rules

- Parsers are pure functions with no side effects and no database access
- Return `null` if notification does not match (not an error)
- Amount must be parsed to cents: `Math.round(parseFloat(match) * 100)`
- Always include the raw notification text for debug logging
- Use named capture groups in regex: `(?<amount>[\d,.]+)`
- Write tests BEFORE writing the parser (TDD)
- Test parsers with real notification samples stored in `__tests__/fixtures/`
- Deduplication happens outside parsers using (amount + currency + timestamp + source) hash

